[codex]   revision-analysis\_r2_review\manuscript_gdoc_text.txt:50:Study 1 mirrored a real organizational practice currently 
[codex] deployed by NPR and provides initial evidence that descriptive feedback about the gender composition of past 
[codex] selections can increase the subsequent selection of women, more so than feedback about other attributes. In our next 
[codex] study, we examine whether our effects hold when people make real, consequential decisions in the field rather than 
[codex] hypothetical choices in an online survey.
