[codex] > This null moderation pattern is suggestive that descriptive feedback operates across partisan lines, consistent with field-experiment evidence that women and racial minorities benefited similarly from explicitly naming their demographic identity when contacting Republican and Democratic city councilors, an effect mediated by motivation to control prejudice (Kirgios et al., 2022).
[codex] >
[codex] > Study 4BΓÇÖs political-ideology null is consistent with this broader account, suggesting that external motivation to control prejudice and internal motivation to control prejudice may both operate across the political spectrum.
[codex] 
[codex] Why this wording: The first sentence interprets the Study 4B null without claiming proof from a null result. The second sentence ties that null to the two forms of motivation in the General Discussion, as requested.
